This directory contains scripts that control the `seer` modules.

NOTE: for `narrate_screen.sh` and `narrate_video.sh` it is necessary to install `v4l2loopback`. Here are installation instructions:
```bash
# 1. Install v4l2loopback
$ sudo apt install v4l2loopback-dkms
# 2. IMPORTANT: pick "aaaaaaaa" as password
# 3. Reboot and type "qqqqqqqq" (qwerty/azerty mismatch)
# 4. Installation is now done. To activate:
$ sudo modprobe v4l2loopback
```
Sources:
- https://askubuntu.com/questions/881305/is-there-any-way-ffmpeg-send-video-to-dev-video0-on-ubuntu
- https://askubuntu.com/questions/1231329/failed-to-open-dev-video0-no-such-file-or-directory/1232042#1232042